Document_summary: This document is an application for approval of a Power Purchase Agreement between Hawaiian Electric Company, Inc. and Kalaeloa Solar Two, LLC. It outlines the terms and conditions of the agreement, including the construction and operation of a 5 MW photovoltaic energy facility. The implications include meeting Hawaii's Renewable Energy Portfolio Standards and reducing reliance on fossil fuels.

This document is an application for approval of a Power Purchase Agreement (PPA) between Hawaiian Electric Company, Inc. and Kalaeloa Solar Two, LLC. The PPA includes provisions for the purchase of as-available energy and the construction of interconnection facilities. The document outlines the terms and conditions of the PPA, including pricing structures, renewable energy goals, and interconnection requirements.

This document is an application by Hawaiian Electric Company seeking approval for a Power Purchase Agreement with Waiawa PV, LLC for a 45.9 MW AC net photovoltaic project. The application emphasizes the importance of timely approval to meet construction milestones and highlights the benefits of the project in meeting renewable energy goals in Hawaii.

This document is a revised Community-Based Renewable Energy Program Phase 1, outlining the availability, customer participation, credit rates, O&M fees, developer participation, and requirements for participation in the CBRE Program. It sets forth eligibility criteria for residential and commercial customers, limits on purchasing interests in CBRE Program Facilities, upfront payments, O&M fees, and credit rates.
Suggested_title_v3: 11-30-2015 Community-Based Renewable Energy Program Phase 1 Revision

Document_summary: This document is an application for approval of a Power Purchase Agreement (PPA) for a renewable dispatchable generation project in Hawaii. The PPA aims to increase renewable energy utilization, reduce fossil fuel consumption, and meet the State's energy policy goals. The document outlines the project details, community outreach efforts, financial impacts, and requests for approvals from the Public Utilities Commission.
